  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mathematics Teacher (Full Time)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Us:</strong></p><p><br />We are a growing tuition centre dedicated to nurturing young learners through engaging, structured, and effective lessons. We focus on helping students build a strong foundation in Mathematics while developing confidence and problem-solving skills.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Teach <strong>k1 to Primary 6 Mathematics</strong> based on the <strong>MOE (Singapore)</strong> syllabus</li><li>Plan and conduct engaging lessons in accordance with Spark Minds Education's curriculum</li><li>Mark and review students’ work to track progress.</li><li>Prepare teaching materials, worksheets, and assessments.</li><li>Communicate regularly with parents on student progress.</li><li>Foster a positive and motivating learning environment.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma, preferably in Education, Mathematics or a related field.</li><li>Minimum <strong>1 year</strong> of teaching or tutoring experience with primary school students preferred</li><li>Both home tutoring and tuition centre teachers are welcome to apply</li><li>Strong knowledge of Singapore’s MOE Primary Math syllabus.</li><li>Passionate, patient, and able to engage children effectively.</li><li>Good communication and classroom management skills.</li></ul><p><strong>We Offer:</strong></p><ul><li>Competitive remuneration</li><li>Structured curriculum and training support</li><li>Warm supportive teaching environment</li><li>Opportunities for growth within the centre</li></ul><p>📧 <strong>To Apply:</strong><br />Please send your resume by clicking \"apply\" or email resume to <strong>sparkmindslearninghub@gmail.com</strong> with the subject “Application – Math Teacher (Full Time)”</p>",
